whole gluten intolerance thing.

00:04:10.870 --> 00:04:13.070 align:middle line:84%
But there is
another possibility.

00:04:13.070 --> 00:04:15.871 align:middle line:90%
What if I have celiac disease?

00:04:15.871 --> 00:04:19.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Celiac disease is an
autoimmune disease in which

00:04:19.450 --> 00:04:22.270 align:middle line:84%
the lining of the
intestine-- the villi--

00:04:22.270 --> 00:04:24.310 align:middle line:90%
begin attacking themselves.

00:04:24.310 --> 00:04:27.640 align:middle line:84%
And people lose the ability
to absorb nutrients,

00:04:27.640 --> 00:04:28.840 align:middle line:90%
and essentially starve.

00:04:28.840 --> 00:04:33.350 align:middle line:84%
>> 130 people or so are thought
to be at risk for celiac

00:04:33.350 --> 00:04:34.150 align:middle line:90%
disease.

00:04:34.150 --> 00:04:35.140 align:middle line:90%
That's huge.

00:04:35.140 --> 00:04:38.680 align:middle line:90%
One out of 130 is incredible.

00:04:38.680 --> 00:04:41.005 align:middle line:84%
>> So, I decided to
get tested for celiac.

00:04:41.005 --> 00:04:43.590 align:middle line:90%


00:04:43.590 --> 00:04:46.350 align:middle line:84%
Celiac disease is
four times more common

00:04:46.350 --> 00:04:49.620 align:middle line:90%
than it was in the 1950s.

00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:53.560 align:middle line:84%
