00:06:41.310 --> 00:06:43.115 align:middle line:90%
30 now.

00:06:43.115 --> 00:06:47.710 align:middle line:84%
>> One grain to 30 per
stalk is a big change.

00:06:47.710 --> 00:06:50.488 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to see it for myself.

00:06:50.488 --> 00:06:53.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Wheat.

00:06:53.410 --> 00:06:56.580 align:middle line:84%
And to grow the wheat,
it takes a farmer.

00:06:56.580 --> 00:07:00.790 align:middle line:84%
From New York to Michigan
to Nebraska to Oregon

00:07:00.790 --> 00:07:03.670 align:middle line:84%
and from the Dakotas down
through all the great grain

00:07:03.670 --> 00:07:08.460 align:middle line:84%
belt, 1,000, 10,000
and 100,000 wheat

00:07:08.460 --> 00:07:10.820 align:middle line:84%
farmers grow the
finest of wheat.

00:07:10.820 --> 00:07:15.221 align:middle line:90%


00:07:15.221 --> 00:07:19.700 align:middle line:84%
>> In this country, almost all
bread is made from this hard

00:07:19.700 --> 00:07:22.130 align:middle line:90%
red winter wheat.

00:07:22.130 --> 00:07:25.040 align:middle line:84%
