00:10:01.330 --> 00:10:03.370 align:middle line:84%
to feed their armies,
would have had to grind

00:10:03.370 --> 00:10:06.150 align:middle line:90%
immense quantities of grain.

00:10:06.150 --> 00:10:09.070 align:middle line:84%
A waterwheel is another
1,000 years later,

00:10:09.070 --> 00:10:14.340 align:middle line:84%
so that technology
comes in around 1000 AD.

00:10:14.340 --> 00:10:19.806 align:middle line:84%
By the early 19th century, there
is roller technology in place.

00:10:19.806 --> 00:10:23.670 align:middle line:84%
>> So if milling technology
has changed so much,

00:10:23.670 --> 00:10:26.250 align:middle line:84%
I wonder what that means
for the wheat itself?

00:10:26.250 --> 00:10:30.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, wheat is good for us
