00:10:30.110 --> 00:10:31.010 align:middle line:90%
form.

00:10:31.010 --> 00:10:34.400 align:middle line:84%
All parts of the seed have
everything a life needs.

00:10:34.400 --> 00:10:37.460 align:middle line:84%
Has bran-- which the
fiber is a very good food

00:10:37.460 --> 00:10:39.210 align:middle line:90%
for the microbes in your body.

00:10:39.210 --> 00:10:41.330 align:middle line:90%
Has energy in the endosperm.

00:10:41.330 --> 00:10:44.810 align:middle line:84%
It has various oils
in the germ, so it's

00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:47.180 align:middle line:90%
an incredibly nutritious food.

00:10:47.180 --> 00:10:49.880 align:middle line:84%
But I hasten to add,
this is not how Americans

00:10:49.880 --> 00:10:52.142 align:middle line:90%
eat bread or wheat anymore.

00:10:52.142 --> 00:10:57.340 align:middle line:90%


00:10:57.340 --> 00:10:59.370 align:middle line:90%
95%-- at least--

00:10:59.370 --> 00:11:02.460 align:middle line:84%
of the wheat that we
eat has been refined,

00:11:02.460 --> 00:11:04.480 align:middle line:84%
which is to say the
bran and the germ--

00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:07.050 align:middle line:90%
the two healthiest parts--

00:11:07.050 --> 00:11:08.490 align:middle line:90%
are discarded.

00:11:08.490 --> 00:11:13.525 align:middle line:84%
And we pig out on
the white flour.

00:11:13.525 --> 00:11:17.300 align:middle line:84%
>> That bran and germ helped
us digest gluten in the first

00:11:17.300 --> 00:11:18.710 align:middle line:90%
place.

00:11:18.710 --> 00:11:22.850 align:middle line:84%
