00:11:34.070 --> 00:11:36.260 align:middle line:84%
and we sell it
back to people who

00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:38.990 align:middle line:84%
are starved of nutrients
in the form of vitamins.

00:11:38.990 --> 00:11:40.020 align:middle line:90%
It's brilliant.

00:11:40.020 --> 00:11:43.530 align:middle line:84%
It's a great business model,
but it's terrible nutrition.

00:11:43.530 --> 00:11:45.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Originally,
this didn't happen.

00:11:45.480 --> 00:11:49.250 align:middle line:84%
Originally, every little
town had its own mill there.

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:51.930 align:middle line:84%
It was usually a stone
mill, and you'd go down

00:11:51.930 --> 00:11:53.820 align:middle line:84%
and you'd pick up
a bag of flour.

00:11:53.820 --> 00:11:56.340 align:middle line:84%
That would be whole ground, and
so it had all the nutrition.

00:11:56.340 --> 00:12:00.450 align:middle line:84%
The downside is it had all
this-- the natural oils

00:12:00.450 --> 00:12:03.480 align:middle line:84%
that are in the
wheat germ itself,

00:12:03.480 --> 00:12:06.060 align:middle line:84%
and those oils will
go bad over time.

00:12:06.060 --> 00:12:08.670 align:middle line:90%
They become rancid.

00:12:08.670 --> 00:12:12.420 align:middle line:84%
With the growth of our
nation and the food industry,

00:12:12.420 --> 00:12:13.980 align:middle line:84%
started shipping
products everywhere

00:12:13.980 --> 00:12:15.690 align:middle line:90%
over the United States.

00:12:15.690 --> 00:12:19.050 align:middle line:90%
That became untenable.

00:12:19.050 --> 00:12:21.112 align:middle line:84%
And then somebody
figured out how to do it.

00:12:21.112 --> 00:12:23.070 align:middle line:84%
They invented these things
called roller mills.

00:12:23.070 --> 00:12:26.360 align:middle line:90%


00:12:26.360 --> 00:12:30.230 align:middle line:84%
It breaks off the bran and the
germ, and that's thrown out.

00:12:30.230 --> 00:12:33.920 align:middle line:84%
Now you had this
white flour that you

00:12:33.920 --> 00:12:35.540 align:middle line:90%
could ship all over the world.

00:12:35.540 --> 00:12:37.160 align:middle line:90%
It wouldn't go bad.

00:12:37.160 --> 00:12:39.440 align:middle line:84%
It was one of the biggest
changes to the human diet

00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:41.320 align:middle line:90%
since cooking was invented.

00:12:41.320 --> 00:12:45.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Except that white
flour is making me sick.

00:12:45.830 --> 00:12:47.690 align:middle line:90%
What about whole wheat flour?

00:12:47.690 --> 00:12:50.060 align:middle line:84%
If all the parts of the
wheat seed are still there,

00:12:50.060 --> 00:12:54.324 align:middle line:84%
then shouldn't whole
wheat flour be OK for me?

00:12:54.324 --> 00:12:58.990 align:middle line:84%
>> There is another
shortcut that one can take.

00:12:58.990 --> 00:13:03.130 align:middle line:84%
If you want to claim that
your product is whole grain

00:13:03.130 --> 00:13:06.760 align:middle line:84%
but you have to buy flour from
the commercial roller mill

00:13:06.760 --> 00:13:09.220 align:middle line:84%
industry, you have
the capability

00:13:09.220 --> 00:13:13.240 align:middle line:84%
to add back your own bran or
your own part of the germ.

00:13:13.240 --> 00:13:16.000 align:middle line:90%
So that's done, to some degree.

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:20.620 align:middle line:84%
Some places add just the bran
back so that they can then

00:13:20.620 --> 00:13:22.450 align:middle line:90%
claim, oh, this is whole grain.

00:13:22.450 --> 00:13:23.770 align:middle line:90%
But is it really whole grain?

00:13:23.770 --> 00:13:24.985 align:middle line:90%
No, not really.

00:13:24.985 --> 00:13:29.620 align:middle line:84%
>> So whole wheat flour is
actually just white flour with

00:13:29.620 --> 00:13:32.170 align:middle line:90%
some bran thrown back in?

00:13:32.170 --> 00:13:34.900 align:middle line:84%
Then, I found out that this
way of milling and marketing

00:13:34.900 --> 00:13:36.070 align:middle line:90%
is very American.

00:13:36.070 --> 00:13:38.400 align:middle line:84%
And they don't do
that in Europe?

00:13:38.400 --> 00:13:39.900 align:middle line:90%
>> They don't do that in Europe.

00:13:39.900 --> 00:13:40.730 align:middle line:90%
>> What do they do?

00:13:40.730 --> 00:13:45.362 align:middle line:84%
>> They take the whole grain,
and they mill it whole.

00:13:45.362 --> 00:13:47.897 align:middle line:84%
>> So they don't take the
bran out and the germ.

00:13:47.897 --> 00:13:49.730 align:middle line:84%
>> They don't take the
bran or the germ out.

00:13:49.730 --> 00:13:50.550 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:13:50.550 --> 00:13:53.490 align:middle line:84%
What they do is,
they mill it whole

00:13:53.490 --> 00:13:56.580 align:middle line:84%
and then if there's large
particles, they sift it off.

00:13:56.580 --> 00:13:58.380 align:middle line:90%
>> This whole milling--

00:13:58.380 --> 00:14:01.362 align:middle line:84%
or stone ground milling,
as it's called--

00:14:01.362 --> 00:14:02.820 align:middle line:84%
is basically what
we had been doing

00:14:02.820 --> 00:14:06.350 align:middle line:84%
for centuries before
roller mills were invented.

00:14:06.350 --> 00:14:08.400 align:middle line:84%
And in some places,
they still use it.

00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:13.440 align:middle line:84%
>> If you go to France and you
get your breads from a baker

00:14:13.440 --> 00:14:20.220 align:middle line:84%
that uses whole milled flour,
or flour that's been processed

00:14:20.220 --> 00:14:24.250 align:middle line:84%
through whole milling,
then you can eat it.

00:14:24.250 --> 00:14:27.810 align:middle line:84%
>> This may sound crazy, but
what Mark was saying seemed

00:14:27.810 --> 00:14:29.610 align:middle line:90%
to make sense.

00:14:29.610 --> 00:14:31.350 align:middle line:84%
When I lived in France
three years ago,

00:14:31.350 --> 00:14:33.180 align:middle line:90%
I had no problem eating bread.

00:14:33.180 --> 00:14:35.610 align:middle line:84%
But as soon as I got
back to the States,

00:14:35.610 --> 00:14:37.660 align:middle line:90%
