00:16:12.910 --> 00:16:15.130 align:middle line:84%
which wouldn't be a big
deal if we were sticking

00:16:15.130 --> 00:16:17.650 align:middle line:90%
to the traditional recipe.

00:16:17.650 --> 00:16:21.391 align:middle line:84%
But today's bread is a
bit more complicated.

00:16:21.391 --> 00:16:26.000 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't like this ingredient,
high fructose of corn syrup,

00:16:26.000 --> 00:16:33.820 align:middle line:84%
wheat, gluten, soy beans, and-or
cottonseed oils, salt, honey,

00:16:33.820 --> 00:16:37.890 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE] ascorbic acid.

00:16:37.890 --> 00:16:39.550 align:middle line:90%
>> The list went on.

00:16:39.550 --> 00:16:42.730 align:middle line:84%
How had we gotten so far away
from just those three simple

00:16:42.730 --> 00:16:44.950 align:middle line:84%
ingredients, flour,
water, and salt?

00:16:44.950 --> 00:16:48.798 align:middle line:90%


00:16:48.798 --> 00:16:52.980 align:middle line:84%
>> We'd taken this very healthy
food and we'd processed it

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:55.530 align:middle line:84%
to the point where it was
not only less nutritious,

00:16:55.530 --> 00:16:56.910 align:middle line:90%
