00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:18.970 align:middle line:84%
And interesting, so whiteness
always equated with wealth.

00:18:18.970 --> 00:18:22.900 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
that changes only

00:18:22.900 --> 00:18:26.107 align:middle line:84%
when the technology is able to
make mass produced white bread,

00:18:26.107 --> 00:18:27.190 align:middle line:90%
and then it becomes cheap.

00:18:27.190 --> 00:18:35.640 align:middle line:90%


00:18:35.640 --> 00:18:38.600 align:middle line:84%
The industrial Wonder Bread
kind of sliced white bread

00:18:38.600 --> 00:18:41.630 align:middle line:84%
then becomes a mark of
being low class, which

00:18:41.630 --> 00:18:43.330 align:middle line:90%
is totally, totally, opposite.

00:18:43.330 --> 00:18:44.478 align:middle line:90%
Switches entirely.

00:18:44.478 --> 00:18:50.094 align:middle line:90%


00:18:50.094 --> 00:18:53.510 align:middle line:84%
>> I found out about Chad
Robertson and his San Francisco

00:18:53.510 --> 00:18:54.460 align:middle line:90%
bakery, Tartine.

00:18:54.460 --> 00:18:57.530 align:middle line:90%


00:18:57.530 --> 00:18:59.780 align:middle line:84%
Chad wanted to make a
good loaf of wheat bread

00:18:59.780 --> 00:19:03.740 align:middle line:84%
that was digestible, because
